---
description: Node.js / API rules
globs:
  - "app/api/**/*.ts"
  - "src/services/**/*.ts"
  - "src/repositories/**/*.ts"
  - "server/**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

## Layers (do not merge)
- Route handler: validate → call service → return response
- Service: business logic; no direct DB access
- Repository: queries only; no business rules

## Errors
- Services return `{ data, error }`; avoid throwing for expected failures
- Let the framework handle errors in route handlers; avoid blanket try/catch
- External HTTP calls must use a timeout

## Validation
- Parse all inputs with Zod; on failure respond 400
- Shared schemas in `lib/validators/` for client and server
- Never trust client-supplied ids; authorize before reads/writes

## Database
- Use the ORM/query layer from `stack.md`
- Queries live in `repositories/`, not scattered in services or routes
- Use the ORM’s transaction APIs; avoid raw `BEGIN`/`COMMIT`
- No `SELECT *`; list columns explicitly
